				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Nmi in a nutshell:<br /><br />Nmi is a physical pin on the CPU. What happens when this pin is active is that the CPU stops all current code, and jumps to another piece of code indicated by the <em>nmi vector</em>. Before the jump it pushes the current adress on the stack, to which you can return with the &quot;RTS&quot; instruction.<br /><br />The nmi vector is at adress $FFFA-$FFFB. So you need to place the adress (or label) there in your rom.<br /><br />edit: place this code at the end of your rom<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;.org&nbsp; &nbsp;$FFFA<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;.dw&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; NMI ;(NMI_Routine)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;.dw&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; reset&nbsp; ;(Reset_Routine)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;.dw&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 0 ;(IRQ_Routine)</div><br /><br />If you do that, and then have an nmi label like so:<br /><br />edit2:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">NMI:<br />LDA $2002; reading $2002 will acknowledge NMI happend. THIS IS NOT TO READ THE VBLANK BIT<br />;nmi code goes here</div><br />It should work, also you'll have to turn on NMI first!<br />edit3: to turn on NMI, set bit 7 of $2000</div>

					
